  "prompt": "Which is currently the most affordable city in South Korea (in terms of rent)?",
  "response": "As of October 2023, **Daegu** is often considered one of the most affordable cities in South Korea in terms of rent. Located in the southeastern part of the country, Daegu offers relatively lower housing costs compared to larger metropolitan areas like Seoul, Busan, or Incheon. Other smaller cities like **Gwangju** and **Ulsan** are also known for their affordability.\n\nHere\u2019s a general comparison of average monthly rent for a one-bedroom apartment in city centers (as of recent data):\n\n- **Seoul**: \u20a9800,000\u2013\u20a91,500,000 (approx. $600\u2013$1,100 USD)  \n- **Busan**: \u20a9500,000\u2013\u20a9800,000 (approx. $375\u2013$600 USD)  \n- **Daegu**: \u20a9300,000\u2013\u20a9500,000 (approx. $225\u2013$375 USD)  \n- **Gwangju**: \u20a9300,000\u2013\u20a9450,000 (approx. $225\u2013$340 USD)  \n\nWhile Daegu is currently one of the most affordable, exact costs can vary depending on the neighborhood, property type, and other factors. Smaller towns and rural areas in South Korea will generally be even cheaper, but they may lack the amenities and job opportunities found in larger cities. Always check updated housing market trends for the latest information.",
